{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012cgWVSozGTheo78vbSuExm","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 2.1: Workflow YAML JSON Schema\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a developer,\n8\tI want a JSON schema defining valid workflow YAML structure,\n9\tso that malformed workflows are rejected at parse time with specific error messages.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria\n12\t\n13\t1. **Given** a workflow YAML file with valid `tasks` (each having `agent`, `scope`, `session`, `source_access`) and a valid `flow` array\n14\t   **When** validated against the JSON schema\n15\t   **Then** validation passes with no errors\n16\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n17\t\n18\t2. **Given** a workflow YAML file missing the required `tasks` field\n19\t   **When** validated against the JSON schema\n20\t   **Then** validation fails with an error identifying the missing `tasks` field\n21\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t3. **Given** a workflow YAML file missing the required `flow` field\n24\t   **When** validated against the JSON schema\n25\t   **Then** validation fails with an error identifying the missing `flow` field\n26\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n27\t\n28\t4. **Given** a task with `scope` set to a value other than `per-story` or `per-run`\n29\t   **When** validated against the JSON schema\n30\t   **Then** validation fails with an error identifying the invalid `scope` value\n31\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n32\t\n33\t5. **Given** a task with `session` set to a value other than `fresh` or `continue`\n34\t   **When** validated against the JSON schema\n35\t   **Then** validation fails with an error identifying the invalid `session` value\n36\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n37\t\n38\t6. **Given** a `flow` array containing a `loop:` block that references task names\n39\t   **When** validated against the JSON schema\n40\t   **Then** the `loop:` block structure is accepted as valid (structural validation only; referential integrity check — ensuring task names in `loop` exist in `tasks` — is deferred to the parser module in story 2.2)\n41\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n42\t\n43\t7. **Given** a task missing the required `agent` field\n44\t   **When** validated against the JSON schema\n45\t   **Then** validation fails with an error identifying the missing `agent` field\n46\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n47\t\n48\t8. **Given** the codebase after this story is implemented\n49\t   **When** the project is inspected\n50\t   **Then** the schema file exists at `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json`\n51\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n52\t\n53\t9. **Given** a task with optional fields (`prompt_template`, `input_contract`, `output_contract`, `source_access`, `max_budget_usd`)\n54\t   **When** validated against the JSON schema\n55\t   **Then** all optional fields are accepted when present and validation passes when they are absent\n56\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n57\t\n58\t10. **Given** unit tests for the schema validation\n59\t    **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n60\t    **Then** all schema validation tests pass with 80%+ coverage on the validation utility\n61\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n62\t\n63\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n64\t\n65\t- [x] Task 1: Create `src/schemas/` directory and `workflow.schema.json` (AC: #8)\n66\t  - [x] Create `src/schemas/` directory\n67\t  - [x] Define the JSON schema with `$schema`, `$id`, `type: object`, `required: [tasks, flow]`\n68\t  - [x] Define `tasks` as object with `additionalProperties` referencing a task definition schema\n69\t  - [x] Define task properties: `agent` (string, required), `scope` (enum: per-story, per-run), `session` (enum: fresh, continue), `source_access` (boolean), `prompt_template` (string), `input_contract` (object), `output_contract` (object), `max_budget_usd` (number)\n70\t  - [x] Define `flow` as an array of items that are either strings (task references) or objects with a `loop` key containing an array of strings\n71\t  - [x] Set sensible defaults: `scope: per-story`, `session: fresh`, `source_access: true`\n72\t\n73\t- [x] Task 2: Create schema validation utility (AC: #1-7, #9)\n74\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` (or co-locate in workflow-parser as a standalone validate function)\n75\t  - [x] Use `ajv` for JSON schema validation — or use a zero-dependency approach: hand-written validate function since the schema is small and `ajv` adds ~150KB. Decision: use `ajv` (or `ajv/dist/2020`) for correctness and maintainability; it's a dev-time cost, not a runtime concern for a CLI tool\n76\t  - [x] Export `validateWorkflowYaml(data: unknown): ValidationResult` returning `{ valid: boolean; errors: ValidationError[] }`\n77\t  - [x] Each `ValidationError` includes `path` (JSON pointer), `message` (human-readable), `keyword` (schema keyword that failed)\n78\t  - [x] Load schema from `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json` via `resolveJsonModule`\n79\t\n80\t- [x] Task 3: Write unit tests (AC: #10)\n81\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/__tests__/schema-validate.test.ts` (or `src/schemas/__tests__/workflow-schema.test.ts`)\n82\t  - [x] Test: valid minimal workflow passes (tasks + flow)\n83\t  - [x] Test: valid full workflow with all optional fields passes\n84\t  - [x] Test: missing `tasks` field fails with specific error\n85\t  - [x] Test: missing `flow` field fails with specific error\n86\t  - [x] Test: invalid `scope` value fails with specific error\n87\t  - [x] Test: invalid `session` value fails with specific error\n88\t  - [x] Test: `loop:` block in flow is structurally valid\n89\t  - [x] Test: missing `agent` in task fails with specific error\n90\t  - [x] Test: optional fields accepted when present, pass when absent\n91\t  - [x] Test: `source_access` as non-boolean fails\n92\t  - [x] Test: `max_budget_usd` as non-number fails\n93\t  - [x] Test: empty `tasks` object is valid (degenerate but schema-legal)\n94\t  - [x] Test: empty `flow` array is valid (degenerate but schema-legal)\n95\t  - [x] Target 80%+ coverage on the validation module\n96\t\n97\t## Dev Notes\n98\t\n99\t### This is the FIRST file in `src/schemas/` -- a NEW directory\n100\t\n101\tThe `src/schemas/` directory does not yet exist. Create it. This directory will eventually hold three schemas: `workflow.schema.json` (this story), `agent.schema.json` (story 3.1), and `verdict.schema.json` (story 6.2).\n102\t\n103\t### Schema Must Match the PRD Workflow YAML Shape\n104\t\n105\tThe PRD (prd-evaluator-redesign.md, \"API Surface -- Workflow YAML Schema\" section) defines the YAML shape:\n106\t\n107\t```yaml\n108\t# Default workflow structure (from PRD + architecture)\n109\ttasks:\n110\t  implement:\n111\t    agent: dev\n112\t    scope: per-story\n113\t    session: fresh\n114\t    source_access: true\n115\t    prompt_template: \"Implement story {{story_key}} following the story file...\"\n116\t  verify:\n117\t    agent: evaluator\n118\t    scope: per-run\n119\t    session: fresh\n120\t    source_access: false\n121\t    prompt_template: \"Verify all stories against their ACs...\"\n122\t  retry:\n123\t    agent: dev\n124\t    scope: per-story\n125\t    session: fresh\n126\t    source_access: true\n127\t    prompt_template: \"Fix failures from evaluator findings: {{findings}}\"\n128\t\n129\tflow:\n130\t  - implement\n131\t  - verify\n132\t  - loop:\n133\t    - retry\n134\t    - verify\n135\t```\n136\t\n137\tKey schema elements from the PRD:\n138\t- `tasks` -- named task definitions (object, not array)\n139\t- `flow` -- ordered execution steps, items are either string task references or `loop:` blocks\n140\t- Task properties: `scope` (per-story/per-run), `session` (fresh/continue), `source_access` (boolean), `agent` (string)\n141\t- Optional task properties: `prompt_template`, `input_contract`, `output_contract`, `max_budget_usd`\n142\t\n143\t### Scope of This Story: Schema Only\n144\t\n145\tThis story creates the JSON schema file and a validation utility. It does NOT:\n146\t- Parse YAML (that's story 2.2, workflow-parser)\n147\t- Resolve patches (that's story 9.1)\n148\t- Validate referential integrity (task names in `flow` exist in `tasks`) -- that's a parser concern (story 2.2)\n149\t- Create the default workflow YAML (that's story 2.3)\n150\t\n151\tThe schema validates **structure** -- required fields, types, enums. The parser (2.2) validates **semantics** -- task references, logical consistency.\n152\t\n153\t### JSON Schema Validation Library Decision\n154\t\n155\t**Option A: `ajv`** -- the standard JSON schema validator for Node.js. Correct, battle-tested, supports JSON Schema draft-07/2020-12. Adds ~150KB to node_modules but zero impact on bundle size since tsup tree-shakes.\n156\t\n157\t**Option B: Hand-written validation** -- zero dependencies but more code to maintain, higher bug risk for edge cases.\n158\t\n159\t**Decision: Use `ajv`.** The correctness guarantee outweighs the dependency cost. The `codeharness validate` command (story 2.5) will reuse this same validation path for both workflow and agent schemas. Install with `npm install ajv`.\n160\t\n161\t### Architecture Constraints\n162\t\n163\t- **File location:** `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json` -- per architecture-v2.md project structure\n164\t- **Validation utility location:** `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` -- co-located with other lib modules. This module will be reused by `workflow-parser.ts` (story 2.2) and `validate` command (story 2.5)\n165\t- **YAML key convention:** All keys in the schema use `snake_case` per architecture-v2.md\n166\t- **Export naming:** `camelCase` for functions (`validateWorkflowSchema`), `PascalCase` for types (`ValidationResult`, `ValidationError`)\n167\t- **No `any` in API surface** (NFR18) -- use `unknown` for untyped input data\n168\t- **`resolveJsonModule: true`** already set in tsconfig.json -- JSON schema can be imported directly\n169\t\n170\t### TypeScript Interfaces to Export\n171\t\n172\t```typescript\n173\texport interface ValidationError {\n174\t  path: string;        // JSON pointer, e.g., \"/tasks/implement/scope\"\n175\t  message: string;     // Human-readable, e.g., \"scope must be 'per-story' or 'per-run'\"\n176\t  keyword: string;     // JSON Schema keyword, e.g., \"enum\"\n177\t}\n178\t\n179\texport interface ValidationResult {\n180\t  valid: boolean;\n181\t  errors: ValidationError[];\n182\t}\n183\t```\n184\t\n185\tThese interfaces will be reused by story 2.2 (parser) and story 2.5 (validate command).\n186\t\n187\t### `flow` Array Item Schema\n188\t\n189\tThe `flow` array items are heterogeneous:\n190\t- **String items:** task references (e.g., `\"implement\"`, `\"verify\"`)\n191\t- **Object items:** `loop:` blocks (e.g., `{ loop: [\"retry\", \"verify\"] }`)\n192\t\n193\tIn JSON Schema, this is modeled with `oneOf`:\n194\t```json\n195\t{\n196\t  \"items\": {\n197\t    \"oneOf\": [\n198\t      { \"type\": \"string\" },\n199\t      {\n200\t        \"type\": \"object\",\n201\t        \"required\": [\"loop\"],\n202\t        \"properties\": {\n203\t          \"loop\": {\n204\t            \"type\": \"array\",\n205\t            \"items\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n206\t            \"minItems\": 1\n207\t          }\n208\t        },\n209\t        \"additionalProperties\": false\n210\t      }\n211\t    ]\n212\t  }\n213\t}\n214\t```\n215\t\n216\t### Error Reporting\n217\t\n218\tErrors must be specific enough for the `codeharness validate` command (story 2.5) to report \"file path, line context, and specific violation\" per FR45 AC. The schema validation provides the `path` and `message`; line context mapping is the parser's job (story 2.2).\n219\t\n220\t### Testing Standards\n221\t\n222\t- Framework: vitest (already configured)\n223\t- Pattern: `describe`/`it`/`expect`\n224\t- Test location: `src/lib/__tests__/schema-validate.test.ts` or `src/schemas/__tests__/workflow-schema.test.ts` -- prefer `src/lib/__tests__/` to match established pattern\n225\t- No mocks needed -- pure validation logic\n226\t- Coverage target: 80%+ on the validation module\n227\t\n228\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n229\t\n230\tStory 1.3 (workflow-state-module) established:\n231\t- `yaml` package import: `import { parse, stringify } from 'yaml'`\n232\t- `node:fs` import: `import { existsSync, mkdirSync, readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs'`\n233\t- `warn()` from `src/lib/output.ts` for non-fatal warnings\n234\t- Code review renamed `readState`/`writeState` to `readWorkflowState`/`writeWorkflowState` to avoid namespace collision -- apply similar namespace-awareness when naming exports from this module\n235\t\n236\t### Git Intelligence\n237\t\n238\tRecent commits follow pattern: `feat: story {key} -- {description}`. The codebase builds and tests cleanly after story 1.3. No pending rework needed before this story.\n239\t\n240\tRelevant commit: `39ec40c feat: story 1-3-workflow-state-module` -- workflow-state.ts is the foundation module this story builds adjacent to.\n241\t\n242\t### What Downstream Modules Need From This Story\n243\t\n244\t- **Story 2.2 (workflow-parser):** Will import the schema and validation function to validate parsed YAML\n245\t- **Story 2.5 (validate command):** Will import the validation function for the CLI command\n246\t- **Story 3.1 (agent schema):** Will follow the same pattern established here for `agent.schema.json`\n247\t- **Story 6.2 (verdict schema):** Same pattern for `verdict.schema.json`\n248\t\n249\tDesign the validation API to be schema-agnostic where possible -- the `validateAgainstSchema(data, schema)` pattern is preferable to `validateWorkflow(data)` so the same function works for all three schemas.\n250\t\n251\t### Project Structure Notes\n252\t\n253\t- New directory: `src/schemas/` -- aligns with architecture-v2.md project structure\n254\t- New file: `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json`\n255\t- New file: `src/lib/schema-validate.ts`\n256\t- New file: `src/lib/__tests__/schema-validate.test.ts`\n257\t- New dependency: `ajv` (add to package.json dependencies)\n258\t- No changes to existing files beyond AGENTS.md\n259\t\n260\t### References\n261\t\n262\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 2.1: Workflow YAML JSON Schema]\n263\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD1: Module Boundaries -- workflow-parser]\n264\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Project Structure & Boundaries -- src/schemas/]\n265\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Implementation Patterns & Consistency Rules]\n266\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#API Surface -- Workflow YAML Schema]\n267\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR1, FR2, FR5]\n268\t\n269\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n270\t## Verification Requirements\n271\t\n272\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/2-1-workflow-yaml-json-schema-proof.md)\n273\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n274\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (80%)\n275\t\n276\t## Documentation Requirements\n277\t\n278\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n279\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/2-1-workflow-yaml-json-schema.md\n280\t\n281\t## Testing Requirements\n282\t\n283\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n284\t- [ ] Coverage target: 80%\n285\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n286\t\n287\t## Dev Agent Record\n288\t\n289\t### Agent Model Used\n290\tclaude-opus-4-6 (1M context)\n291\t\n292\t### Debug Log References\n293\tNone — no debugging required.\n294\t\n295\t### Completion Notes List\n296\t- Used `ajv` (added as production dependency) for JSON Schema draft-07 validation\n297\t- Exported both `validateWorkflowSchema` (workflow-specific) and `validateAgainstSchema` (generic, reusable for agent/verdict schemas in stories 3.1 and 6.2)\n298\t- 24 tests covering all acceptance criteria, edge cases, type errors, and structural validation\n299\t- Coverage: 100% statements, 100% functions, 100% lines, 75% branches on schema-validate.ts (exceeds 80% target)\n300\t- Named export `validateWorkflowSchema` (not `validateWorkflowYaml` as story spec suggested) to match the actual function — it validates parsed data, not YAML strings\n301\t\n302\t### File List\n303\t- `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json` (new) — JSON Schema for workflow YAML\n304\t- `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` (new) — validation utility with ajv\n305\t- `src/lib/__tests__/schema-validate.test.ts` (new) — 24 unit tests\n306\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Tuyo7ARsiRwTfcugHgbJ4e","session_id":"06dc1e0b-83a0-4950-9e66-ec9396bae461","uuid":"82a93fe2-38a2-49bf-86d9-ebdc5bfb63c5","timestamp":"2026-04-02T11:26:08.918Z"}
