{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Tuyo7ARsiRwTfcugHgbJ4e","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file created at `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-2-workflow-parser-module.md`.\n\n**Summary:**\n\n- **Story:** 2.2 Workflow Parser Module\n- **Key:** `2-2-workflow-parser-module`\n- **Status:** ready-for-dev\n- **File:** `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-2-workflow-parser-module.md`\n\n**What the story covers:**\n- `parseWorkflow(filePath)` function that reads YAML from disk, parses it, validates against the JSON schema (reusing story 2.1's `validateWorkflowSchema`), performs referential integrity checks (task names in `flow` exist in `tasks`), applies defaults, and returns a typed `ResolvedWorkflow` object\n- Custom `WorkflowParseError` class with structured error details\n- Full TypeScript interfaces: `ResolvedWorkflow`, `ResolvedTask`, `FlowStep`, `LoopBlock`\n- 10 acceptance criteria, all tagged `test-provable` (no runtime, environment, or escalation needed -- pure parsing logic)\n\n**Verification tier assignments:**\nAll 10 ACs are `test-provable` -- the entire module is pure parsing/validation logic that can be fully verified by building and running unit tests with no running app or environment.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **No problems encountered.** All artifacts (epics-v2, architecture-v2, previous story 2-1, schema files) were found and loaded cleanly.\n- **Workaround:** The BMAD config file was at `_bmad/config.yaml`, not `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` as the workflow suggested -- the glob resolved this without issue.\n- **Risk:** AC #6 (500ms performance) is trivially met for small files but the test could be flaky on slow CI runners. The story notes this is a wall-clock assertion.\n- **Observation:** Story 2.1's completion notes mention that `ajv` does NOT apply defaults to input data (it validates but doesn't mutate). The parser must explicitly apply