{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0148PDta7xjN6fU1uQ1bMsnP","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 2.2: Workflow Parser Module\n2\t\n3\tStatus: ready-for-dev\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want a workflow-parser module that loads YAML from disk, validates it against the JSON schema, resolves task references, and returns a typed config object,\n11\tso that the workflow engine receives a fully validated, resolved workflow definition it can execute without further parsing.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a valid workflow YAML file on disk\n16\t   **When** `parseWorkflow(filePath)` is called\n17\t   **Then** the file is read, parsed as YAML, validated against the workflow JSON schema, and a typed `ResolvedWorkflow` object is returned containing `tasks` and `flow`\n18\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n19\t\n20\t2. **Given** a workflow YAML file containing invalid YAML syntax (e.g., bad indentation, unclosed quotes)\n21\t   **When** `parseWorkflow(filePath)` is called\n22\t   **Then** it throws a `WorkflowParseError` with a message identifying the YAML syntax problem\n23\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t3. **Given** a workflow YAML file that is valid YAML but fails JSON schema validation (e.g., missing `tasks`, invalid `scope` value)\n26\t   **When** `parseWorkflow(filePath)` is called\n27\t   **Then** it throws a `WorkflowParseError` whose message includes all schema validation errors (path and message for each)\n28\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n29\t\n30\t4. **Given** a workflow YAML file where a `flow` step (string or `loop:` item) references a task name not defined in `tasks`\n31\t   **When** `parseWorkflow(filePath)` is called\n32\t   **Then** it throws a `WorkflowParseError` identifying each dangling task reference\n33\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t5. **Given** a workflow YAML file where a `loop:` block inside `flow` references task names that all exist in `tasks`\n36\t   **When** `parseWorkflow(filePath)` is called\n37\t   **Then** the `loop:` block is included in the resolved flow as a `LoopBlock` object with its task list\n38\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n39\t\n40\t6. **Given** a valid workflow YAML file\n41\t   **When** `parseWorkflow(filePath)` is called and the wall-clock duration is measured\n42\t   **Then** parsing completes in <500ms (NFR1)\n43\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n44\t\n45\t7. **Given** a file path that does not exist\n46\t   **When** `parseWorkflow(filePath)` is called\n47\t   **Then** it throws a `WorkflowParseError` with a message indicating the file was not found\n48\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n49\t\n50\t8. **Given** the `ResolvedWorkflow` return type\n51\t   **When** inspected\n52\t   **Then** it includes typed interfaces: `ResolvedWorkflow` (with `tasks: Record<string, ResolvedTask>` and `flow: FlowStep[]`), `ResolvedTask` (all task properties from the schema), and `FlowStep` (union of `string | LoopBlock`)\n53\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n54\t\n55\t9. **Given** unit tests for the workflow-parser module\n56\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n57\t   **Then** all tests pass with 80%+ coverage on `workflow-parser.ts`\n58\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n59\t\n60\t10. **Given** the codebase after this story is implemented\n61\t    **When** the project is inspected\n62\t    **Then** the module exists at `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` with co-located tests at `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-parser.test.ts`\n63\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n64\t\n65\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n66\t\n67\t- [ ] Task 1: Define TypeScript interfaces (AC: #8)\n68\t  - [ ] Create `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts`\n69\t  - [ ] Define `ResolvedTask` interface matching all task schema properties: `agent` (string), `scope` (enum string), `session` (enum string), `source_access` (boolean), `prompt_template?` (string), `input_contract?` (object), `output_contract?` (object), `max_budget_usd?` (number)\n70\t  - [ ] Define `LoopBlock` interface: `{ loop: string[] }`\n71\t  - [ ] Define `FlowStep` type: `string | LoopBlock`\n72\t  - [ ] Define `ResolvedWorkflow` interface: `{ tasks: Record<string, ResolvedTask>; flow: FlowStep[] }`\n73\t  - [ ] Define `WorkflowParseError` class extending `Error` with `errors` property for structured error details\n74\t  - [ ] Export all types and the error class\n75\t\n76\t- [ ] Task 2: Implement `parseWorkflow()` function (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #5, #6, #7)\n77\t  - [ ] Read file from disk with `readFileSync` -- throw `WorkflowParseError` if file not found\n78\t  - [ ] Parse YAML using `parse()` from the `yaml` package -- catch YAML parse errors and wrap in `WorkflowParseError`\n79\t  - [ ] Validate parsed data against workflow schema using `validateWorkflowSchema()` from `schema-validate.ts` -- throw `WorkflowParseError` with all schema errors if invalid\n80\t  - [ ] Perform referential integrity check: collect all task name references from `flow` (both string items and `loop:` block items) and verify each exists as a key in `tasks` -- throw `WorkflowParseError` listing dangling references\n81\t  - [ ] Apply defaults: `scope` defaults to `'per-story'`, `session` defaults to `'fresh'`, `source_access` defaults to `true` (matching JSON schema defaults)\n82\t  - [ ] Return typed `ResolvedWorkflow` object\n83\t\n84\t- [ ] Task 3: Write unit tests (AC: #9, #10)\n85\t  - [ ] Create `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-parser.test.ts`\n86\t  - [ ] Test: valid minimal workflow (tasks + flow) returns `ResolvedWorkflow`\n87\t  - [ ] Test: valid full workflow with all optional fields returns correctly typed result\n88\t  - [ ] Test: defaults applied when optional fields omitted (`scope`, `session`, `source_access`)\n89\t  - [ ] Test: invalid YAML syntax throws `WorkflowParseError` with YAML error info\n90\t  - [ ] Test: valid YAML but fails schema (missing `tasks`) throws with schema errors\n91\t  - [ ] Test: valid YAML but fails schema (invalid `scope` enum) throws with schema errors\n92\t  - [ ] Test: flow references non-existent task throws with dangling reference message\n93\t  - [ ] Test: loop block references non-existent task throws with dangling reference message\n94\t  - [ ] Test: loop block with valid references resolves correctly\n95\t  - [ ] Test: file not found throws with file-not-found message\n96\t  - [ ] Test: parsing completes in <500ms for a typical workflow\n97\t  - [ ] Test: empty tasks object with empty flow is valid (degenerate but schema-legal)\n98\t  - [ ] Test: `WorkflowParseError` includes structured errors array\n99\t  - [ ] Target 80%+ coverage\n100\t\n101\t## Dev Notes\n102\t\n103\t### Module Location and Architecture Role\n104\t\n105\t`src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` is the second module in the 7-module dependency chain: workflow-state -> **workflow-parser** -> agent-resolver -> agent-dispatch -> workflow-engine -> evaluator -> circuit-breaker.\n106\t\n107\tThe parser sits between the JSON schema (story 2.1) and the workflow engine (epic 5). It is the only module that touches the filesystem for workflow YAML; all downstream consumers receive a typed `ResolvedWorkflow` object.\n108\t\n109\t### Reuse `schema-validate.ts` from Story 2.1\n110\t\n111\tStory 2.1 created `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` with:\n112\t- `validateWorkflowSchema(data: unknown): ValidationResult` -- validates parsed data against the workflow JSON schema\n113\t- `ValidationResult` -- `{ valid: boolean; errors: ValidationError[] }`\n114\t- `ValidationError` -- `{ path: string; message: string; keyword: string }`\n115\t\n116\tImport and call `validateWorkflowSchema()` after YAML parsing. Do NOT reimplement schema validation. The schema itself lives at `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json`.\n117\t\n118\t### Referential Integrity Check (Deferred from Story 2.1)\n119\t\n120\tStory 2.1 explicitly deferred referential integrity validation to this story (see 2.1 AC #6: \"referential integrity check -- ensuring task names in `loop` exist in `tasks` -- is deferred to the parser module in story 2.2\"). This is the semantic validation layer that goes beyond JSON schema structural validation.\n121\t\n122\tCollect all task name references from `flow`:\n123\t- String items are direct task references\n124\t- `loop:` blocks contain arrays of task references\n125\t\n126\tCompare each reference against `Object.keys(tasks)`. Any reference not found is a dangling reference error.\n127\t\n128\t### Default Value Application\n129\t\n130\tThe JSON schema declares defaults (`scope: \"per-story\"`, `session: \"fresh\"`, `source_access: true`), but `ajv` in its current configuration does not mutate the input to apply defaults. The parser must explicitly apply these defaults to tasks that omit them. This ensures the `ResolvedWorkflow` object always has complete task definitions.\n131\t\n132\t### Error Handling Pattern\n133\t\n134\tUse a custom error class (`WorkflowParseError`) to distinguish parser errors from other errors. The error should carry structured information so that downstream consumers (e.g., the `validate` command in story 2.5) can format errors with file paths and context.\n135\t\n136\t```typescript\n137\texport class WorkflowParseError extends Error {\n138\t  public readonly errors: Array<{ path: string; message: string }>;\n139\t  constructor(message: string, errors?: Array<{ path: string; message: string }>) {\n140\t    super(message);\n141\t    this.name = 'WorkflowParseError';\n142\t    this.errors = errors ?? [];\n143\t  }\n144\t}\n145\t```\n146\t\n147\t### Established Patterns from Previous Stories\n148\t\n149\tFrom `workflow-state.ts` (story 1.3):\n150\t- `import { parse } from 'yaml'` for YAML parsing\n151\t- `import { readFileSync, existsSync } from 'node:fs'` for file I/O\n152\t- `warn()` from `src/lib/output.ts` for non-fatal warnings\n153\t- Function naming: `camelCase` (e.g., `readWorkflowState`, `writeWorkflowState`)\n154\t\n155\tFrom `schema-validate.ts` (story 2.1):\n156\t- `import { validateWorkflowSchema } from './schema-validate.js'`\n157\t- `ValidationResult`, `ValidationError` types already defined there\n158\t\n159\t### Performance Requirement (NFR1)\n160\t\n161\tNFR1 requires workflow YAML parsing and validation in <500ms. For a typical workflow file (~50 lines), this should be trivially met. The test should measure wall-clock time of `parseWorkflow()` and assert <500ms.\n162\t\n163\t### What This Story Does NOT Do\n164\t\n165\t- **Patch resolution** (embedded -> user -> project chain): That is story 9.1. This parser loads a single YAML file. The engine (epic 5) will call `parseWorkflow()` with the already-resolved file path.\n166\t- **Create the default workflow YAML**: That is story 2.3.\n167\t- **CLI `validate` command**: That is story 2.5, which will call `parseWorkflow()` and format errors.\n168\t- **Agent resolution**: That is story 3.3 (agent-resolver).\n169\t\n170\t### Architecture Constraints\n171\t\n172\t- **File location:** `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` per architecture-v2.md\n173\t- **YAML key convention:** All keys use `snake_case` per architecture\n174\t- **Export naming:** `camelCase` for functions, `PascalCase` for types/interfaces\n175\t- **No `any` in API surface** (NFR18) -- use `unknown` for untyped input\n176\t- **Dependencies:** Only `yaml` (already installed) and `schema-validate.ts` (story 2.1). No new npm dependencies needed.\n177\t\n178\t### Downstream Consumers\n179\t\n180\t- **Story 2.5 (validate command):** Will call `parseWorkflow()` and catch `WorkflowParseError` for error reporting\n181\t- **Story 5.1 (flow execution):** Will call `parseWorkflow()` to get the resolved workflow for engine execution\n182\t- **Story 9.1 (workflow patch resolution):** Will extend this module with patch resolution logic\n183\t\n184\t### Project Structure Notes\n185\t\n186\t- New file: `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts`\n187\t- New file: `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-parser.test.ts`\n188\t- No new directories needed\n189\t- No new npm dependencies needed\n190\t- No changes to existing files except `src/lib/AGENTS.md` (add workflow-parser entry)\n191\t\n192\t### References\n193\t\n194\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 2.2: Workflow Parser Module]\n195\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD1: Module Boundaries -- workflow-parser]\n196\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Implementation Patterns & Consistency Rules]\n197\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Project Structure & Boundaries -- src/lib/]\n198\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-1-workflow-yaml-json-schema.md -- schema-validate.ts API, ajv defaults behavior]\n199\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR1, FR5, NFR1]\n200\t\n201\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n202\t## Verification Requirements\n203\t\n204\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/2-2-workflow-parser-module-proof.md)\n205\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n206\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (80%)\n207\t\n208\t## Documentation Requirements\n209\t\n210\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n211\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/2-2-workflow-parser-module.md\n212\t\n213\t## Testing Requirements\n214\t\n215\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n216\t- [ ] Coverage target: 80%\n217\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n218\t\n219\t## Dev Agent Record\n220\t\n221\t### Agent Model Used\n222\t\n223\t{{agent_model_name_version}}\n224\t\n225\t### Debug Log References\n226\t\n227\t### Completion Notes List\n228\t\n229\t### File List\n230\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"06dc1e0b-83a0-4950-9e66-ec9396bae461","uuid":"2ad566b1-78f8-41c0-bded-a88daaf613fb","timestamp":"2026-04-02T11:28:17.614Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-2-workflow-parser-module.md","content":"# Story 2.2: Workflow Parser Module\n\nStatus: ready-for-dev\n\n<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer,\nI want a workflow-parser module that loads YAML from disk, validates it against the JSON schema, resolves task references, and returns a typed config object,\nso that the workflow engine receives a fully validated, resolved workflow definition it can execute without further parsing.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **Given** a valid workflow YAML file on disk\n   **When** `parseWorkflow(filePath)` is called\n   **Then** the file is read, parsed as YAML, validated against the workflow JSON schema, and a typed `ResolvedWorkflow` object is returned containing `tasks` and `flow`\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n2. **Given** a workflow YAML file containing invalid YAML syntax (e.g., bad indentation, unclosed quotes)\n   **When** `parseWorkflow(filePath)` is called\n   **Then** it throws a `WorkflowParseError` with a message identifying the YAML syntax problem\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n3. **Given** a workflow YAML file that is valid YAML but fails JSON schema validation (e.g., missing `tasks`, invalid `scope` value)\n   **When** `parseWorkflow(filePath)` is called\n   **Then** it throws a `WorkflowParseError` whose message includes all schema validation errors (path and message for each)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n4. **Given** a workflow YAML file where a `flow` step (string or `loop:` item) references a task name not defined in `tasks`\n   **When** `parseWorkflow(filePath)` is called\n   **Then** it throws a `WorkflowParseError` identifying each dangling task reference\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n5. **Given** a workflow YAML file where a `loop:` block inside `flow` references task names that all exist in `tasks`\n   **When** `parseWorkflow(filePath)` is called\n   **Then** the `loop:` block is included in the resolved flow as a `LoopBlock` object with its task list\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n6. **Given** a valid workflow YAML file\n   **When** `parseWorkflow(filePath)` is called and the wall-clock duration is measured\n   **Then** parsing completes in <500ms (NFR1)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n7. **Given** a file path that does not exist\n   **When** `parseWorkflow(filePath)` is called\n   **Then** it throws a `WorkflowParseError` with a message indicating the file was not found\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n8. **Given** the `ResolvedWorkflow` return type\n   **When** inspected\n   **Then** it includes typed interfaces: `ResolvedWorkflow` (with `tasks: Record<string, ResolvedTask>` and `flow: FlowStep[]`), `ResolvedTask` (all task properties from the schema), and `FlowStep` (union of `string | LoopBlock`)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n9. **Given** unit tests for the workflow-parser module\n   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n   **Then** all tests pass with 80%+ coverage on `workflow-parser.ts`\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n10. **Given** the codebase after this story is implemented\n    **When** the project is inspected\n    **Then** the module exists at `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` with co-located tests at `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-parser.test.ts`\n    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [ ] Task 1: Define TypeScript interfaces (AC: #8)\n  - [ ] Create `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts`\n  - [ ] Define `ResolvedTask` interface matching all task schema properties: `agent` (string), `scope` (enum string), `session` (enum string), `source_access` (boolean), `prompt_template?` (string), `input_contract?` (object), `output_contract?` (object), `max_budget_usd?` (number)\n  - [ ] Define `LoopBlock` interface: `{ loop: string[] }`\n  - [ ] Define `FlowStep` type: `string | LoopBlock`\n  - [ ] Define `ResolvedWorkflow` interface: `{ tasks: Record<string, ResolvedTask>; flow: FlowStep[] }`\n  - [ ] Define `WorkflowParseError` class extending `Error` with `errors` property for structured error details\n  - [ ] Export all types and the error class\n\n- [ ] Task 2: Implement `parseWorkflow()` function (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #5, #6, #7)\n  - [ ] Read file from disk with `readFileSync` -- throw `WorkflowParseError` if file not found\n  - [ ] Parse YAML using `parse()` from the `yaml` package -- catch YAML parse errors and wrap in `WorkflowParseError`\n  - [ ] Validate parsed data against workflow schema using `validateWorkflowSchema()` from `schema-validate.ts` -- throw `WorkflowParseError` with all schema errors if invalid\n  - [ ] Perform referential integrity check: collect all task name references from `flow` (both string items and `loop:` block items) and verify each exists as a key in `tasks` -- throw `WorkflowParseError` listing dangling references\n  - [ ] Apply defaults: `scope` defaults to `'per-story'`, `session` defaults to `'fresh'`, `source_access` defaults to `true` (matching JSON schema defaults)\n  - [ ] Return typed `ResolvedWorkflow` object\n\n- [ ] Task 3: Write unit tests (AC: #9, #10)\n  - [ ] Create `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-parser.test.ts`\n  - [ ] Test: valid minimal workflow (tasks + flow) returns `ResolvedWorkflow`\n  - [ ] Test: valid full workflow with all optional fields returns correctly typed result\n  - [ ] Test: defaults applied when optional fields omitted (`scope`, `session`, `source_access`)\n  - [ ] Test: invalid YAML syntax throws `WorkflowParseError` with YAML error info\n  - [ ] Test: valid YAML but fails schema (missing `tasks`) throws with schema errors\n  - [ ] Test: valid YAML but fails schema (invalid `scope` enum) throws with schema errors\n  - [ ] Test: flow references non-existent task throws with dangling reference message\n  - [ ] Test: loop block references non-existent task throws with dangling reference message\n  - [ ] Test: loop block with valid references resolves correctly\n  - [ ] Test: file not found throws with file-not-found message\n  - [ ] Test: parsing completes in <500ms for a typical workflow\n  - [ ] Test: empty tasks object with empty flow is valid (degenerate but schema-legal)\n  - [ ] Test: `WorkflowParseError` includes structured errors array\n  - [ ] Target 80%+ coverage\n\n## Dev Notes\n\n### Module Location and Architecture Role\n\n`src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` is the second module in the 7-module dependency chain: workflow-state -> **workflow-parser** -> agent-resolver -> agent-dispatch -> workflow-engine -> evaluator -> circuit-breaker.\n\nThe parser sits between the JSON schema (story 2.1) and the workflow engine (epic 5). It is the only module that touches the filesystem for workflow YAML; all downstream consumers receive a typed `ResolvedWorkflow` object.\n\n### Reuse `schema-validate.ts` from Story 2.1\n\nStory 2.1 created `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` with:\n- `validateWorkflowSchema(data: unknown): ValidationResult` -- validates parsed data against the workflow JSON schema\n- `ValidationResult` -- `{ valid: boolean; errors: ValidationError[] }`\n- `ValidationError` -- `{ path: string; message: string; keyword: string }`\n\nImport and call `validateWorkflowSchema()` after YAML parsing. Do NOT reimplement schema validation. The schema itself lives at `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json`.\n\n### Referential Integrity Check (Deferred from Story 2.1)\n\nStory 2.1 explicitly deferred referential integrity validation to this story (see 2.1 AC #6: \"referential integrity check -- ensuring task names in `loop` exist in `tasks` -- is deferred to the parser module in story 2.2\"). This is the semantic validation layer that goes beyond JSON schema structural validation.\n\nCollect all task name references from `flow`:\n- String items are direct task references\n- `loop:` blocks contain arrays of task references\n\nCompare each reference against `Object.keys(tasks)`. Any reference not found is a dangling reference error.\n\n### Default Value Application\n\nThe JSON schema declares defaults (`scope: \"per-story\"`, `session: \"fresh\"`, `source_access: true`), but `ajv` in its current configuration does not mutate the input to apply defaults. The parser must explicitly apply these defaults to tasks that omit them. This ensures the `ResolvedWorkflow` object always has complete task definitions.\n\n### Error Handling Pattern\n\nUse a custom error class (`WorkflowParseError`) to distinguish parser errors from other errors. The error should carry structured information so that downstream consumers (e.g., the `validate` command in story 2.5) can format errors with file paths and context.\n\n```typescript\nexport class WorkflowParseError extends Error {\n  public readonly errors: Array<{ path: string; message: string }>;\n  constructor(message: string, errors?: Array<{ path: string; message: string }>) {\n    super(message);\n    this.name = 'WorkflowParseError';\n    this.errors = errors ?? [];\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Established Patterns from Previous Stories\n\nFrom `workflow-state.ts` (story 1.3):\n- `import { parse } from 'yaml'` for YAML parsing\n- `import { readFileSync, existsSync } from 'node:fs'` for file I/O\n- `warn()` from `src/lib/output.ts` for non-fatal warnings\n- Function naming: `camelCase` (e.g., `readWorkflowState`, `writeWorkflowState`)\n\nFrom `schema-validate.ts` (story 2.1):\n- `import { validateWorkflowSchema } from './schema-validate.js'`\n- `ValidationResult`, `ValidationError` types already defined there\n\n### Performance Requirement (NFR1)\n\nNFR1 requires workflow YAML parsing and validation in <500ms. For a typical workflow file (~50 lines), this should be trivially met. The test should measure wall-clock time of `parseWorkflow()` and assert <500ms.\n\n### What This Story Does NOT Do\n\n- **Patch resolution** (embedded -> user -> project chain): That is story 9.1. This parser loads a single YAML file. The engine (epic 5) will call `parseWorkflow()` with the already-resolved file path.\n- **Create the default workflow YAML**: That is story 2.3.\n- **CLI `validate` command**: That is story 2.5, which will call `parseWorkflow()` and format errors.\n- **Agent resolution**: That is story 3.3 (agent-resolver).\n\n### Architecture Constraints\n\n- **File location:** `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` per architecture-v2.md\n- **YAML key convention:** All keys use `snake_case` per architecture\n- **Export naming:** `camelCase` for functions, `PascalCase` for types/interfaces\n- **No `any` in API surface** (NFR18) -- use `unknown` for untyped input\n- **Dependencies:** Only `yaml` (already installed) and `schema-validate.ts` (story 2.1). No new npm dependencies needed.\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n- **Story 2.5 (validate command):** Will call `parseWorkflow()` and catch `WorkflowParseError` for error reporting\n- **Story 5.1 (flow execution):** Will call `parseWorkflow()` to get the resolved workflow for engine execution\n- **Story 9.1 (workflow patch resolution):** Will extend this module with patch resolution logic\n\n### Project Structure Notes\n\n- New file: `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts`\n- New file: `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-parser.test.ts`\n- No new directories needed\n- No new npm dependencies needed\n- No changes to existing files except `src/lib/AGENTS.md` (add workflow-parser entry)\n\n### References\n\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 2.2: Workflow Parser Module]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD1: Module Boundaries -- workflow-parser]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Implementation Patterns & Consistency Rules]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Project Structure & Boundaries -- src/lib/]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-1-workflow-yaml-json-schema.md -- schema-validate.ts API, ajv defaults behavior]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR1, FR5, NFR1]\n\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n## Verification Requirements\n\n- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/2-2-workflow-parser-module-proof.md)\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n- [ ] Test coverage meets target (80%)\n\n## Documentation Requirements\n\n- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/2-2-workflow-parser-module.md\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n- [ ] Coverage target: 80%\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n\n## Dev Agent Record\n\n### Agent Model Used\n\n{{agent_model_name_version}}\n\n### Debug Log References\n\n### Completion Notes List\n\n### File List\n","numLines":230,"startLine":1,"totalLines":230}}}
