{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Gd9qFzXVXfLYY9NFdth6a9","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# src/lib — Shared Libraries\n2\t\n3\tPure library modules consumed by CLI commands (`src/commands/`) and by each other. No CLI entry points, no side effects on import.\n4\t\n5\t## State & Output\n6\t\n7\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n8\t|------|---------|-------------|\n9\t| state.ts | YAML front-matter state persistence in `.claude/codeharness.local.md` | `readState`, `writeState`, `readStateWithBody`, `getStatePath`, `HarnessState` |\n10\t| workflow-state.ts | Workflow execution state persistence in `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml` — tracks task checkpoints, evaluator scores, circuit breaker | `readWorkflowState`, `writeWorkflowState`, `getDefaultWorkflowState`, `WorkflowState`, `TaskCheckpoint`, `EvaluatorScore`, `CircuitBreakerState` |\n11\t| output.ts | Structured `[OK]/[FAIL]/[WARN]/[INFO]` CLI output with JSON mode | `ok`, `fail`, `warn`, `info`, `jsonOutput` |\n12\t\n13\t## Stack Provider System\n14\t\n15\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n16\t|------|---------|-------------|\n17\t| stacks/types.ts | Canonical stack type definitions and `StackProvider` interface | `StackProvider`, `StackName`, `AppType`, `CoverageToolName`, `CoverageToolInfo`, `OtlpResult`, `TestCounts` |\n18\t| stacks/registry.ts | Provider registry with marker-based stack detection | `registerProvider`, `getStackProvider`, `detectStacks`, `detectStack`, `StackDetection`, `_resetRegistry` |\n19\t| stacks/nodejs.ts | Full NodejsProvider — all Node.js-specific logic extracted from consumer files | `NodejsProvider` |\n20\t| stacks/python.ts | Full PythonProvider — all Python-specific logic (app type detection, coverage, OTLP, Dockerfile, pytest parsing) | `PythonProvider` |\n21\t| stacks/rust.ts | Full RustProvider — Cargo.toml parsing, tarpaulin coverage, OTLP packages, multi-stage Dockerfile, workspace test aggregation | `RustProvider` |\n22\t| stacks/utils.ts | Shared helpers for stack providers — JSON/text file reading, Node.js/Python/Cargo dependency extraction | `readJsonSafe`, `readTextSafe`, `getNodeDeps`, `getPythonDepsContent`, `hasPythonDep`, `getCargoDepsSection`, `hasCargoDep` |\n23\t| stacks/index.ts | Barrel re-exports + auto-registers NodejsProvider, PythonProvider, RustProvider on import | all public API from types.ts and registry.ts |\n24\t\n25\t## Stack & Environment (Legacy)\n26\t\n27\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n28\t|------|---------|-------------|\n29\t| stack-detect.ts | Legacy stack detection — re-exports `StackName`, `AppType` from stacks/types.ts for backward compat | `detectStack`, `detectAppType`, `AppType` |\n30\t| stack-path.ts | XDG-compliant paths for shared observability stack | `getStackDir`, `getComposeFilePath`, `ensureStackDir` |\n31\t| templates.ts | File generation with `{{var}}` mustache-style rendering | `generateFile`, `renderTemplate` |\n32\t\n33\t## Docker (src/lib/docker/)\n34\t\n35\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n36\t|------|---------|-------------|\n37\t| docker/index.ts | Barrel re-exports for docker subsystem | all public API from compose, health, cleanup |\n38\t| docker/compose.ts | Docker Compose lifecycle — start/stop shared stack, collector | `startStack`, `stopStack`, `startSharedStack`, `stopSharedStack`, `startCollectorOnly`, `stopCollectorOnly`, `isStackRunning`, `isSharedStackRunning`, `isCollectorRunning` |\n39\t| docker/health.ts | Docker health checks, availability, remote probing | `isDockerAvailable`, `isDockerComposeAvailable`, `getStackHealth`, `getCollectorHealth`, `checkRemoteEndpoint`, `DockerHealthResult` |\n40\t| docker/cleanup.ts | Container cleanup utilities | `cleanupOrphanedContainers`, `cleanupVerifyEnv` |\n41\t\n42\t## Observability / OTLP (src/lib/observability/)\n43\t\n44\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n45\t|------|---------|-------------|\n46\t| observability/index.ts | Barrel re-exports for OTLP subsystem | all public API from instrument, config, backends |\n47\t| observability/instrument.ts | OTLP instrumentation — package install, script patching | `installNodeOtlp`, `installPythonOtlp`, `installRustOtlp`, `instrumentProject`, `patchNodeStartScript` |\n48\t| observability/config.ts | OTLP env var configuration for CLI/web/agent modes | `configureOtlpEnvVars`, `ensureServiceNameEnvVar`, `ensureEndpointEnvVar`, `configureCli`, `configureWeb`, `configureAgent` |\n49\t| observability/backends.ts | Observability backend interface with Victoria and ELK implementations | `ObservabilityBackend`, `VictoriaBackend`, `ElkBackend` |\n50\t\n51\t## Schema Validation\n52\t\n53\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n54\t|------|---------|-------------|\n55\t| schema-validate.ts | JSON Schema validation using ajv — workflow YAML structure validation with typed error reporting | `validateWorkflowSchema`, `validateAgainstSchema`, `ValidationResult`, `ValidationError` |\n56\t\n57\t## Coverage & Testing\n58\t\n59\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n60\t|------|---------|-------------|\n61\t| coverage.ts | Coverage tool detection (Vitest/c8/coverage.py/cargo-tarpaulin), execution, evaluation, per-file floors | `detectCoverageTool`, `runCoverage`, `checkOnlyCoverage`, `evaluateCoverage`, `checkPerFileCoverage`, `getTestCommand` |\n62\t\n63\t## Verification Pipeline\n64\t\n65\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n66\t|------|---------|-------------|\n67\t| verify-parser.ts | Parses story ACs with type classification (ui/api/db/general) | `parseStoryACs`, `classifyAC`, `ParsedAC` |\n68\t| verify.ts | Verification orchestrator — preconditions, proof quality validation, Showboat, state | `checkPreconditions`, `validateProofQuality`, `ProofQuality`, `createProofDocument`, `runShowboatVerify`, `closeBeadsIssue`, `proofHasContent` (deprecated) |\n69\t| verify-env.ts | Black-box verification environment — Docker image build (npm pack/pip install), clean workspace prep, env check, cleanup | `buildVerifyImage`, `prepareVerifyWorkspace`, `checkVerifyEnv`, `cleanupVerifyEnv`, `computeDistHash`, `isValidStoryKey` |\n70\t| verifier-session.ts | Black-box verifier session spawner — runs `claude --print` in clean workspace, returns `Result<VerifyResult>`, copies proof back to project | `spawnVerifierSession`, `copyProofToProject` |\n71\t\n72\t## Documentation Health (src/lib/doc-health/)\n73\t\n74\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n75\t|------|---------|-------------|\n76\t| doc-health/index.ts | Barrel re-exports for doc-health subsystem | all public API from scanner, staleness, report |\n77\t| doc-health/scanner.ts | Module detection and doc health scanning | `findModules`, `scanDocHealth`, `DocHealthResult`, `DocHealthReport` |\n78\t| doc-health/staleness.ts | Staleness checks, AGENTS.md completeness, story freshness | `isDocStale`, `getSourceFilesInModule`, `getMentionedFilesInAgentsMd`, `checkAgentsMdCompleteness`, `checkAgentsMdForModule`, `checkDoNotEditHeaders`, `checkStoryDocFreshness` |\n79\t| doc-health/report.ts | Doc health output formatting and exec-plan lifecycle | `formatDocHealthOutput`, `printDocHealthOutput`, `createExecPlan`, `completeExecPlan`, `getExecPlanStatus` |\n80\t| doc-health/types.ts | Shared types for doc-health subsystem | `DocHealthResult`, `ModuleDocHealth`, `SOURCE_EXTENSIONS` |\n81\t\n82\t## Retrospective Parsing & Retro-to-Sprint Pipeline\n83\t\n84\t| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n85\t|------|---------|-------------|\n86\t| retro-parser.ts | Retro markdown parser — action item extraction, classification, priority derivation, section parsing, deduplication | `parseRetroActionItems`, `parseRetroSections`, `normalizeText`, `wordOverlap`, `isDuplicate`, `classifyFinding`, `derivePriority`, `RetroActionItem`, `RetroSectionItem`, `Classification` |\n87\t| retro-to-sprint.ts | Retro-to-sprint pipeline — processes retro action items into TD stories and backlog entries | `processRetroActionItems`, `ensureEpicTd`, `createTdStory`, `nextTdStoryNumber`, `generateSl