n proof document had wrong format — had to be rewritten to match expected `## AC N: Title` format.\n42\t\n43\t### Severity Distribution\n44\t\n45\t| Severity | Count | Fixed? |\n46\t|----------|-------|--------|\n47\t| HIGH | 1 | Yes |\n48\t| MEDIUM | 3 | 2 fixed, 1 deferred (package.json stale entries) |\n49\t| LOW | 2 | Deferred (stubs, dead test suites) |\n50\t\n51\t---\n52\t\n53\t## Cost Analysis\n54\t\n55\t### Session Tool Usage (This Session Only — Story 1-2 Review + Verification)\n56\t\n57\t`codeharness stats` could not run — ralph/session-logs directory was deleted as part of story 1-2. Cost data is reconstructed from subagent token reports in the session issues log.\n58\t\n59\t**Code Review phase (1-2):**\n60\t\n61\t| Tool | Calls |\n62\t|------|-------|\n63\t| Bash | 12 |\n64\t| Read | 13 |\n65\t| Edit | 8 |\n66\t| Grep | 3 |\n67\t| Glob | 4 |\n68\t| Skill | 1 |\n69\t| **Total** | **29** |\n70\t\n71\tLargest Bash outputs: `git diff --name-only` (~250 lines), `git ls-files ralph/` (~250 lines), `git status --porcelain` (~80 lines).\n72\t\n73\t**Verification phase (1-2):**\n74\t\n75\t| Tool | Calls |\n76\t|------|-------|\n77\t| Bash | 14 |\n78\t| Read | 3 |\n79\t| Grep | 4 |\n80\t| Write | 1 |\n81\t| **Total** | **20** |\n82\t\n83\tLargest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~30 lines), `npm run lint` (~20 lines), `npm run build` (~15 lines).\n84\t\n85\t### Session Total: 49 tool calls across 2 phases\n86\t\n87\t### Full-Day Subagent Breakdown (All of Story 1-1 + 1-2)\n88\t\n89\t| Phase | Story | Tool Calls | Heaviest Tools |\n90\t|-------|-------|-----------|----------------|\n91\t| create-story | 1-1 | 16 | Read: 8, Bash: 4 |\n92\t| dev-story | 1-1 | 67 | Edit: 28, Read: 22 |\n93\t| code-review | 1-1 | 30 | Read: 18, Edit: 9 |\n94\t| verification | 1-1 | 6 | Bash: 4, Read: 3 |\n95\t| create-story | 1-2 | 12 | Bash: 4, Read: 4 |\n96\t| dev-story | 1-2 | 53 | Edit: 28, Read: 18 |\n97\t| code-review | 1-2 | 29 | Read: 13, Bash: 12 |\n98\t| verification | 1-2 | 20 | Bash: 14, Grep: 4 |\n99\t| **Total** | | **233** | |\n100\t\n101\t### Token Waste Hotspots\n102\t\n103\t1. **`run.test.ts` read 4 times** at different offsets during 1-2 dev — file was too large for single read.\n104\t2. **Test suite run 3 times** during 1-2 dev — first two runs caught missed references.\n105\t3. **`git diff --stat HEAD~1` run twice** during 1-2 verification — redundant.\n106\t4. **1-1 dev had 2 unnecessary test re-runs** due to missed beads references in first pass.\n107\t5. **`npm run test:unit` output at ~600 lines** in 1-2 dev — largest single Bash output of the day. Should pipe through `tail` or `--silent`.\n108\t\n109\t---\n110\t\n111\t## What Went Well\n112\t\n113\t1. **Both deletion stories completed successfully.** 1-1 (beads) and 1-2 (ralph/hooks/legacy) are done. The codebase is now free of both beads and ralph dependencies.\n114\t2. **Code review caught real bugs.** The review phases found HIGH-severity issues (incomplete ralph deletion, broken stats.ts path, dead type members) that would have been shipped without review.\n115\t3. **Coverage held above floor.** 96.78% overall, all 147 remaining files above the 80% per-file minimum.\n116\t4. **Create-story risk predictions were accurate.** Both stories correctly predicted the `src/lib/state.ts` dependency problem and the scope of changes needed.\n117\t5. **Net LOC strongly negative.** -656,265 lines removed (mostly ralph/logs), achieving NFR17's code-reduction goal.\n118\t6. **Verification was fast.** Both stories passed verification on first attempt after code review fixes.\n119\t\n120\t---\n121\t\n122\t## What Went Wrong\n123\t\n124\t1. **Story spec had incorrect file path.** `src/templates/ralph-prompt.ts` vs actual `src/lib/agents/ralph-prompt.ts` — spec was written from memory, not verified.\n125\t2. **Story spec listed `src/lib/state.ts` for deletion** despite 14+ active importers. Dev agent had to make a judgment call to skip it. This could have caused a catastrophic build failure if followed blindly.\n126\t3. **Multiple commands are now stubs/no-ops.** `run`, `applyAllPatches`, `createProofDocument`, `getDriver` — these are by design (Epic 5 rebuilds them), but it means the CLI is partially non-functional until then.\n127\t4. **`codeharness stats` is broken.** Deleting ralph/session-logs means the stats command can no longer find historical data. No cost report can be generated.\n128\t5. **Proof document format mismatch.** Verification had to rewrite the proof to match expected `## AC N: Title` format — the dev/review phases should produce proofs in the correct format.\n129\t\n130\t---\n131\t\n132\t## Lessons Learned\n133\t\n134\t### Patterns to Repeat\n135\t\n136\t- **Create-story risk identification works.** Both stories flagged the real problems before dev started. Keep using the risk analysis step.\n137\t- **Code review as a separate phase catches real issues.** The HIGH-severity ralph directory cleanup miss and the stats.ts broken path were both caught here, not in dev.\n138\t- **Pure-deletion stories with `test-provable` ACs are efficient.** Both stories moved quickly because the acceptance criteria were binary (code exists or it doesn't).\n139\t\n140\t### Patterns to Avoid\n141\t\n142\t- **Story specs listing files for deletion without verifying import count.** Always run `grep -r \"from.*module\"` before listing a file for deletion.\n143\t- **Large test file reads at multiple offsets.** `run.test.ts` was read 4 times. Consider splitting large test files or using targeted grep instead.\n144\t- **Running full test suite without `--silent` or `tail`.** 600-line test output is wasteful. Pipe through `tail -20` unless debugging.\n145\t- **Assuming the stats command will work after deleting its data source.** Should have saved stats before deleting ralph.\n146\t\n147\t---\n148\t\n149\t## Action Items\n150\t\n151\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner |\n152\t|---|--------|----------|-------|\n153\t| 1 | Fix `package.json` `files` array — 