7\t| 2-1-workflow-yaml-json-schema | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification | done | First Epic 2 story; JSON Schema + ajv validation |\n348\t\n349\t**Sprint progress after session:** Epic 1 fully done (3/3). Epic 2 started — story 2-1 done, 2-2 through 2-5 remain in backlog.\n350\t\n351\t---\n352\t\n353\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n354\t\n355\t### Issues from Story 2-1 (from .session-issues.md)\n356\t\n357\t**Spec/Config Gaps (3)**\n358\t- `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` does not exist — create-story agent inferred config from file locations.\n359\t- Technical workflow engine research document referenced in epics-v2.md does not exist locally.\n360\t- Implementation artifact paths inferred, not read from a config source.\n361\t\n362\t**Code Quality Issues Found by Review (2)**\n363\t- **HIGH (fixed):** Branch coverage 75% on `schema-validate.ts` — `??` fallback paths in error mapping never tested. Review added 4 fake validator tests to reach 100% branch coverage.\n364\t- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `require()` calls in ESM test file — replaced with fake validator pattern.\n365\t\n366\t**Deferred Items (2)**\n367\t- **LOW:** No barrel re-export for `schema-validate.ts` — downstream imports directly. Not blocking.\n368\t- **LOW:** Module-level Ajv singleton pays compilation cost at import time. Negligible for CLI usage.\n369\t\n370\t**Naming Deviation (1)**\n371\t- Story spec said `validateWorkflowYaml` but dev used `validateWorkflowSchema` — function validates parsed JS objects, not YAML strings. Pragmatically correct but diverges from spec.\n372\t\n373\t**ajv Dependency Decision (1)**\n374\t- Story spec said dev-time cost, but validation runs at CLI runtime (story 2-5 `validate` command), so `ajv` was correctly added as a production dependency.\n375\t\n376\t**Verification Format Problems (1)**\n377\t- Proof document required 3 rewrites: wrong headers (`### AC` instead of `## AC`), then missing evidence format (needs `bash`+`output` code blocks), then finally correct. This is the same format issue seen in Sessions 1 and 2 — it remains unfixed in subagent instructions.\n378\t\n379\t### Severity Distribution\n380\t\n381\t| Severity | Count | Fixed? |\n382\t|----------|-------|--------|\n383\t| HIGH | 1 | Yes (branch coverage) |\n384\t| MEDIUM | 1 | Yes (ESM require) |\n385\t| LOW | 3 | Deferred |\n386\t\n387\t---\n388\t\n389\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n390\t\n391\t### This Session (Story 2-1 + orchestrator overhead)\n392\t\n393\tFrom `codeharness stats --save`:\n394\t\n395\t**Total cost: $15.37** across 119 API calls (covers stories 2-1 and 1-3 in current tracking window).\n396\t\n397\t**Cost by Phase:**\n398\t\n399\t| Phase | Calls | Cost | % of Total |\n400\t|-------|-------|------|------------|\n401\t| verify | 67 | $8.31 | 54.1% |\n402\t| orchestrator | 11 | $2.28 | 14.8% |\n403\t| create-story | 17 | $1.77 | 11.5% |\n404\t| dev-story | 10 | $1.19 | 7.8% |\n405\t| code-review | 9 | $1.04 | 6.8% |\n406\t| retro | 5 | $0.78 | 5.0% |\n407\t\n408\t**Cost by Story:**\n409\t\n410\t| Story | Calls | Cost | % |\n411\t|-------|-------|------|---|\n412\t| 2-1-workflow-yaml-json-schema | 68 | $8.34 | 54.2% |\n413\t| 1-3-workflow-state-module | 47 | $5.48 | 35.6% |\n414\t| unknown (orchestrator overhead) | 4 | $1.56 | 10.1% |\n415\t\n416\t**Cost by Token Type:**\n417\t\n418\t| Type | Tokens | Cost | % |\n419\t|------|--------|------|---|\n420\t| Cache reads | 6,796,708 | $10.20 | 66% |\n421\t| Cache writes | 160,732 | $3.01 | 20% |\n422\t| Output | 28,821 | $2.16 | 14% |\n423\t| Input | 127 | $0.00 | 0% |\n424\t\n425\t### Subagent-Level Breakdown (Story 2-1)\n426\t\n427\tFrom token reports in `.session-issues.md`:\n428\t\n429\t| Phase | Tool Calls | Heaviest Tools | Redundancy |\n430\t|-------|-----------|----------------|------------|\n431\t| create-story | 22 | Read: 8, Bash: 5, Grep: 5, Glob: 5 | None |\n432\t| dev-story | 16 | Bash: 8, Read: 4, Edit: 3, Write: 3 | None |\n433\t| code-review | 18 | Bash: 9, Read: 6, Edit: 3 | vitest coverage run 3x (could be 2x) |\n434\t| verification | ~30 | Across 3 attempts | Proof written 3x, verify run 3x |\n435\t| **Total** | **~86** | | |\n436\t\n437\t### Verification Phase Cost Problem\n438\t\n439\tVerification is **54.1% of total cost** ($8.31 of $15.37). This is consistent with the historical pattern (53.1% reported in Session 2). Breakdown of why:\n440\t\n441\t1. **Verification proof format failures.** Story 2-1 verification required 3 attempts (~30 tool calls) because the proof document format was wrong twice before succeeding. This alone likely accounts for 2/3 of verification cost.\n442\t2. **AGENTS.md precondition failure.** `schema-validate.ts` was missing from AGENTS.md, causing `codeharness verify` to fail. Had to fix and re-run.\n443\t3. **Cache read dominance.** 66% of cost is cache reads (6.8M tokens). Each verification retry re-reads the entire context window.\n444\t\n445\t### Token Waste Hotspots\n446\t\n447\t1. **Proof document written 3 times in verification** — ~$3-4 wasted on retry loops. Root cause: subagents do not have explicit proof format instructions.\n448\t2. **vitest coverage run 3x in code-review** — could have been 2x.\n449\t3. **Orchestrator overhead at $2.28 (14.8%)** — context accumulation across subagent dispatches.\n450\t4. **Cache reads at 66% of cost** — large context window re-reads on every API call. Reducing context size would have outsized cost impact.\n451\t\n452\t### Cost Optimization Opportunities\n453\t\n454\t| Opportunity | Estimated Savings | Effort |\n455\t|-------------|------------------|--------|\n456\t| Fix proof format instructions (eliminate verification retries) | ~$3-4/session (30-40%) | Low — add format spec to verification skill prompt |\n457\t| Add `--no-color` to vitest (eliminate ANSI parsing retries) | ~$0.50/session | Low — one-line change |\n458\t| Reduce verification context window (trim unnecessary files) | ~$1-2/session | Medium — requires context audit |\n459\t| Run coverage once per phase, pipe to file | ~$0.30/session | Low — process change |\n460\t\n461\t---\n462\t\n463\t## 4. What Went Well\n464\t\n465\t1. **Story 2-1 completed end-to-end.** JSON Schema definition, ajv-based validation, 100% branch coverage after review. Clean, test-provable story.\n466\t2. **Code review caught the branch coverage gap.** 75% -> 100% branches by adding fake validator tests for the `??` fallback paths. Review continues to find real issues.\n467\t3. **Dev phase was efficient.** Only 16 tool calls — schema definition + validation + tests in a single focused pass. No redundant operations.\n468\t4. **Create-story phase produced accurate risk predictions.** Flagged ajv dependency decision, YAML indentation sensitivity, and potential over-scoping of referential integrity (deferred to 2-2 per plan).\n469\t5. **Overall coverage held at 96.6%** with all 149 files above 80% floor.\n470\t6. **Epic 2 is now in progress.** First story done, clear path to 2-2 (workflow parser).\n471\t\n472\t---\n473\t\n474\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n475\t\n476\t1. **Verification cost is still >50% of total.** Same pattern as Sessions 1 and 2. The proof format retry loop is the single biggest cost driver and it has not been fixed.\n477\t2. **Proof format issue occurred for the third time today.** Session 1 had it, Session 2 had it, Session 3 had it. Three sessions, same bug, no fix applied.\n478\t3. **Missing config files.** `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` and technical research documents don't exist. Create-story had to infer context — this works but adds fragility.\n479\t4. **Function naming diverged from spec.** `validateWorkflowSchema` vs `validateWorkflowYaml` — minor but indicates spec-to-implementation drift.\n480\t5. **`codeharness stats` only tracks recent sessions.** Earlier sessions (1-1, 1-2 standalone) are not in the cost report because ralph/session-logs was deleted. Full-day cost is understated.\n481\t\n482\t---\n483\t\n484\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n485\t\n486\t### Patterns to Repeat\n487\t\n488\t- **Greenfield modules remain fast.** Story 2-1 dev phase: 16 tool calls. Schema definition + validation + tests is a clean, well-scoped unit of work.\n489\t- **Code review as a separate phase.** Caught the branch coverage gap that dev phase missed. This pattern has caught real issues in every story today.\n490\t- **ajv for JSON Schema validation.** Production dependency decision was correct — validation will run at CLI runtime in story 2-5.\n491\t\n492\t### Patterns to Avoid\n493\t\n494\t- **Not fixing the proof format issue.** Three sessions, same failure, same retry cost. This must be fixed before Session 4.\n495\t- **Not saving stats before deleting data sources.** Still no full-day cost picture because of story 1-2 deletion.\n496\t- **Running vitest coverage 3x in a single phase.** Capture once, parse from captured output.\n497\t\n498\t---\n499\t\n500\t## 7. Action Items\n501\t\n502\t| # | Action | Priority | Status |\n503\t|---|--------|----------|--------|\n504\t| 1 | **FIX: Add proof format specification to verification skill prompt** — must include `## AC N: Title` header format and `bash`+`output` evidence block requirement. This is the #1 cost optimization. | CRITICAL | New — blocks cost reduction |\n505\t| 2 | Fix `package.json` `files` array — remove stale `ralph/**/*.sh` and `ralph/AGENTS.md` | HIGH | Carried x2 |\n506\t| 3 | Fix `codeharness stats` to handle missing session-logs directory | MEDIUM | Carried x2 |\n507\t| 4 | Add `--no-color` to vitest invocations in subagent prompts | MEDIUM | Carried x1 |\n508\t| 5 | Create `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` or document that it is intentionally absent | LOW | New |\n509\t| 6 | Begin story 2-2-workflow-parser-module | HIGH | Next session |\n510\t| 7 | Add barrel re-export for `schema-validate.ts` when story 2-2 needs it | LOW | New |\n511\t\n512\t---\n513\t\n514\t## Full-Day Summary (2026-04-02)\n515\t\n516\t### Stories Completed Today\n517\t\n518\t| # | Story | Epic | Type | Tool Calls | Key Review Findings |\n519\t|---|-------|------|------|-----------|-------------------|\n520\t| 1 | 1-1-delete-beads-integration | 1 | Deletion | ~119 | Dead type members, stale JSDoc |\n521\t| 2 | 1-2-delete-ralph-loop-legacy-verification | 1 | Deletion | ~114 | Incomplete ralph/ deletion, broken stats.ts |\n522\t| 3 | 1-3-workflow-state-module | 1 | Greenfield | 74 | Naming collision, validation gaps |\n523\t| 4 | 2-1-workflow-yaml-json-schema | 2 | Greenfield | ~86 | Branch coverage gap, ESM require |\n524\t| | **Total** | | | **~393** | 12 issues found by review |\n525\t\n526\t### Tracked Cost (Stories 1-3 and 2-1 only)\n527\t\n528\t- **$15.37** from `codeharness stats` (covers 1-3 + 2-1)\n529\t- **~$8-10 estimated** for stories 1-1 + 1-2 (not tracked — session-logs deleted)\n530\t- **Full-day estimated total: ~$23-25**\n531\t\n532\t### Cumulative Sprint Cost\n533\t\n534\t- Historical cumulative: $900.92 (158 stories prior)\n535\t- Today: ~$23-25\n536\t- **Running total: ~$924**\n537\t\n538\t### Top Systemic Issue\n539\t\n540\t**Verification phase consumes >50% of spend.** Root cause: proof format retry loops. Fix: embed explicit format requirements in the verification skill prompt. Estimated savings: 30-40% of session cost ($3-4/session).\n541\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01VPGMpQEKamJYD9N88qkRzB","session_id":"06dc1e0b-83a0-4950-9e66-ec9396bae461","uuid":"8971bda6-5e19-4935-9dd8-822024c3eaf5","timestamp":"2026-04-02T11:41:47.764Z"}
